The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Monday, December 27, 2004 

 Track trials 

 OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT

 Calcutta: Apertivo, Moon Emperor, Absolute Luxury, Santarelle and La Fantasie were impressive from among the following horses exercised on Saturday.

 Outer sand track

 2,200m: Exclusive Affair (C. Alford), Calorific (Shanker) and Anzello (Rb) 3-3s; (600m) 49s; (400m) 33s. The first two were level while the last named finished far behind. Apertivo (C. Alford) and Approved (Shanker) in 2-54s; (600m) 49s; (400m) 33s. Former proved far too good for his companion.

 1,800m: Formal Invitation (Shanker) in 2-19s; (600m) 48s; (400m) 32s. Looking very fit.

 1,600m: Moon Emperor (Rajendra) and Secret Obsession (Kariappa) and Mythical Star (Akhtar) in 1-57; (800m) 58s; (600m) 42s; (400m) 28s. They finished in the order named. The first two were separated by two lengths while the last named was simply outclassed.

 1,400m: Absolute Luxury (J. Gurang), River Rafter (Domingo), Razeen/Falling Feather (C. Alford), Appetina (Shanker) and Storm Trooper/Stardust Melody (Rb) in 1-47s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 30s. They finished in the order named. The second and the third named were level finishing two length behind Absolute Luxury. The rest of the field was no match for the first three. Adderly (Domingo) and Aretino (Rb) in 1-46s; (600m) 48s; (400m) 34s. They were level but the latter was handy. The latter is also coming up following his recent run.

 Santarelle (C. Alford) and Apprise (Domingo) in 1-46s; (600m) 49s; (400m) 32s. Former was easily 2 ls better. May strike soon.

 1,000m: Star Magic (G. Singh) in 1-14s; (600m) 45s; (400m) 30s. Moved attractively. Also looking improved since last win. Advancer (G. Singh) in 1-16s; (600m) 46s; (400m) 30s. Moved very easy. Raging Tide (C. Alford) and Magical Romance (Shanker) in 1-1s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 29s. Former was easily 4 ls better. Note former as an early winner. Allenby (Rb) in 1-21s; (600m) 49s; (400m) 33s. Went very easy. May win soon.

 800m: La Fantasie (Gajender) in 57s; (600m) 44s; (400m) 30s. Was very Impressive. Ignore her recent failures. Secret Desire (Reuben) in 1-0s; (600m) 45s; (400m) 31s. Was unextended throughout. Asian Prince (Reuben) and Grecian Prince (Reuben) in 1-3s; (600m) 47s; (400m) 31s. They finished together but latter was very easy. Capable of winning again.




